==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soss
<hw>Soss</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Souse</er>.]</ety> <def>To fall at once into a chair or seat; to sit
lazily.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Soss
<hw>Soss</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To throw in a negligent or careless
manner; to toss.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Soss
<hw>Soss</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A lazy fellow.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cotgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A heavy fall.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hallowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Soss
<hw>Soss</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sesspol</er>.]</ety>
<def>Anything dirty or muddy; a dirty puddle.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

